 25  /-- The category of R-algebras where R is a commutative
 26  ring is the under category R ↓ CRing. In the categorical
 27  setting we have a forgetful functor R-Alg ⥤ R-Mod.
 28  However here it extends module in order to preserve
 29  definitional equality in certain cases. -/
 30  class algebra (R : Type u) (A : Type v) [comm_ring R] [ring A] extends has_scalar R A :=
